<h1 id="Summary">Summary<a class="anchor-link" href="#Summary"> </a></h1><p>Visualizing Covid-19 patients number in the State of Minnesota using <a href="https://altair-viz.github.io/">altair</a>. The county data is taken from <a href="https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data">New York Times repository</a> .</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Introductions">Introductions<a class="anchor-link" href="#Introductions"> </a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I enjoy browsing through the data provided by the <a href="https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html">Minnesota Department of Health</a> on Covid-19 cases daily. It provides the most up-to-date number of confirmed positive cases in the state. However, to get the historical data is a little <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html">circuitous</a>.</p>
<p>So, I was thrilled to learn that the New York Times published their county-by-county <a href="https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data">Covid-19 data</a> historically. It motivated me to create an interactive map of Minnesota and their historical data on a similar fashion as shown on the <a href="https://covid19dashboards.com/growth-map-us-states/">covid-19 dashboards</a>.</p>
<p>In summary, using a <a href="https://jupyter.org/">Jupyter notebook</a>, I want to showcase <a href="https://fastpages.fast.ai/">fastpages'</a> capacity to visualize interactive map and bar graph in <a href="https://altair-viz.github.io/">Altair</a> using Covid-19 data.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
  (function(spec, embedOpt){
    const outputDiv = document.getElementById("altair-viz-1");
    const paths = {
      "vega": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega@5?noext",
      "vega-lib": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega-lib?noext",
      "vega-lite": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega-lite@4.0.0?noext",
      "vega-embed": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega-embed@6?noext",
    };

    function loadScript(lib) {
      return new Promise(function(resolve, reject) {
        var s = document.createElement('script');
        s.src = paths[lib];
        s.async = true;
        s.onload = () => resolve(paths[lib]);
        s.onerror = () => reject(`Error loading script: ${paths[lib]}`);
        document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(s);
      });
    }

    function showError(err) {
      outputDiv.innerHTML = `<div class="error" style="color:red;">${err}</div>`;
      throw err;
    }

    function displayChart(vegaEmbed) {
      vegaEmbed(outputDiv, spec, embedOpt)
        .catch(err => showError(`Javascript Error: ${err.message}<br>This usually means there's a typo in your chart specification. See the javascript console for the full traceback.`));
    }

    if(typeof define === "function" && define.amd) {
      requirejs.config({paths});
      require(["vega-embed"], displayChart, err => showError(`Error loading script: ${err.message}`));
    } else if (typeof vegaEmbed === "function") {
      displayChart(vegaEmbed);
    } else {
      loadScript("vega")
        .then(() => loadScript("vega-lite"))
        .then(() => loadScript("vega-embed"))
        .catch(showError)
        .then(() => displayChart(vegaEmbed));
    }

<h2 id="Importing-modules">Importing modules<a class="anchor-link" href="#Importing-modules"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I start by importing all the necessary components:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%</span><span class="n">reload_ext</span> <span class="n">autoreload</span>
<span class="o">%</span><span class="n">autoreload</span> <span class="mi">2</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">altair</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">alt</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">requests</span>
</pre></div>
<p>I used <code>%reload_ext autoreload</code> <a href="https://ipython.readthedocs.io/en/stable/config/extensions/autoreload.html">Python magic</a> in order to reload all changed modules <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5364050/reloading-submodules-in-ipython">before executing a new line</a>. Pandas and Altair are used for the data formatting and data visualizations along with <code>requests</code> to obtain the json formatted data.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Data-Extraction-and-Cleaning">Data Extraction and Cleaning<a class="anchor-link" href="#Data-Extraction-and-Cleaning"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="New-York-Times-County-by-county-Data">New York Times County-by-county Data<a class="anchor-link" href="#New-York-Times-County-by-county-Data"> </a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I am getting the data from the New York Times repository and converting it into a pandas DataFrame:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># data from NY-Times:</span>
<span class="n">url</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nytimes/covid-19-data/master/us-counties.csv&quot;</span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">url</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">dfmn</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">state</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="s2">&quot;Minnesota&quot;</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;date&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;date&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>As mentioned on the <a href="https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data">their github repository</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p>Many state health departments choose to report cases separately when the patient’s county of residence is unknown or pending determination. In these instances, we record the county name as “Unknown.” As more information about these cases becomes available, the cumulative number of cases in “Unknown” counties may fluctuate.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I dropped the <code>unknown</code> number of confirmed cases because the number of confirmed cases is higher than reported on the <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html">Minnesota Department of Health web site</a> if I include them.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># drop the null values by first finding the index of the unknown, then use list </span>
<span class="c1"># comprehension to drop the values </span>
<span class="n">unknown</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">any</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;columns&quot;</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span>
<span class="n">dfmn</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">i</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">unknown</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">del</span> <span class="n">unknown</span>
<span class="c1"># now that there is no null value:</span>
<span class="c1"># convert the FIPS as string in integer format to match with the json county data for Minnesota</span>
<span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fips</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fips</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">astype</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">astype</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
<p>However, that is not the case for death counts. The death count discrepancies are on the 27th and the 26th of March. By checking between the Minnesota Department of Health <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html">web archive</a> and our <a href="https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data">New York Times dataset</a>, I decided to add the unknown death count data to Hennepin county. This might not reflect the reality, but adding the data to Hennepin county makes the most sense in order to maintain anonimity and accuracy of the data due to the county having the highest number of cases in the State of Minnesota.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># dealing with discrepancy with the death count: </span>
<span class="c1"># use: https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html</span>
<span class="c1"># and see the difference between the two dates of 03/28 and 03/27</span>
<span class="c1"># 03-28</span>
<span class="c1"># dfmn[(dfmn.date==&quot;2020-03-28&quot;)&amp;(dfmn.deaths != 0)]</span>
<span class="c1"># 03-27</span>
<span class="c1"># dfmn[(dfmn.date==&quot;2020-03-27&quot;)&amp;(dfmn.deaths != 0)]</span>
<span class="c1">#hide</span>
<span class="c1"># let&#39;s add the death data into Hennepin county for 03-27:</span>
<span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loc</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">county</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="s2">&quot;Hennepin&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="s2">&quot;2020-03-27&quot;</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="s1">&#39;deaths&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2</span>
<span class="c1"># new 2020-03-27:</span>
<span class="c1"># dfmn[(dfmn.date==&quot;2020-03-27&quot;)&amp;(dfmn.deaths != 0)]</span>
<span class="c1"># 2020-03-26</span>
<span class="c1"># dfmn[(dfmn.date==&quot;2020-03-26&quot;)&amp;(dfmn.deaths != 0)]</span>
<span class="c1"># I added 1 death data into Hennepin county for 2020-03-26</span>
<span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loc</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">county</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="s2">&quot;Hennepin&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="s2">&quot;2020-03-26&quot;</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="s1">&#39;deaths&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="County-data">County data<a class="anchor-link" href="#County-data"> </a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The topographic and FIPS data is taken from <a href="https://github.com/deldersveld/topojson/tree/master/countries/us-states">David Eldersved's github repository</a>.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># getting minnesota county data</span>
<span class="n">url_counties</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&quot;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/deldersveld/topojson/master/countries/us-states/MN-27-minnesota-counties.json&quot;</span>
<span class="n">resp</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">requests</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">url_counties</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">resp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">json</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="k">del</span> <span class="n">resp</span>
<span class="n">df_county</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">json_normalize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;objects&#39;</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s1">&#39;cb_2015_minnesota_county_20m&#39;</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s1">&#39;geometries&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">df_county</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df_county</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s2">&quot;properties.GEOID&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;properties.NAME&quot;</span><span class="p">]]</span>
<span class="n">df_county</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;fips&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;county&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="k">del</span> <span class="n">data</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Combining-Case-count-and-County-Data">Combining Case count and County Data<a class="anchor-link" href="#Combining-Case-count-and-County-Data"> </a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>We combine the two data sources using for loop:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Remove state column since it is all in Minnesota:</span>
<span class="n">df3mneasy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;state&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># grabbing all the dates in the data for the for loop</span>
<span class="n">uniquedate</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df3mneasy</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">unique</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="c1"># an empty DataFrame for the new data</span>
<span class="n">countycase_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DataFrame</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="c1"># add 0 cases and 0 deaths for counties that do not have cases</span>
<span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span><span class="s1">&#39;cases&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;deaths&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">}</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">uniquedate</span><span class="p">:</span> 
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df3mneasy</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">df3mneasy</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="c1">#filter for each date</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df_county</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;left&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># we want to keep all the counties </span>
    <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;date&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;date&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fillna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># fill the appropriate date</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fillna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">values</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># fill the zero counts</span>
    <span class="n">countycase_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ignore_index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># new DataFrame</span>

<span class="c1"># remove df3mneasy and uniquedate</span>
<span class="k">del</span> <span class="n">df3mneasy</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">uniquedate</span>
<span class="c1"># getting the data for the latest date</span>
<span class="n">dfmnlatest</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="nb">max</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="p">)]</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Counting-New-Cases">Counting New Cases<a class="anchor-link" href="#Counting-New-Cases"> </a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>In order to get the number of new cases, I used pandas dataframe <code>diff</code> to calculate the difference of consecutive rows.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># getting data to see the increment of new cases per day</span>
<span class="n">newcases</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s2">&quot;county&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;date&quot;</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">ascending</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="c1"># grabbing all the county in minnesota</span>
<span class="n">uniquecounty</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">newcases</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">county</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">unique</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="c1"># empty_df for </span>
<span class="n">newcases_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DataFrame</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">uniquecounty</span><span class="p">:</span> 
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">newcases</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">newcases</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">county</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;newcases&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">cases</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;newdeaths&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">deaths</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">newcases_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">newcases_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ignore_index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">del</span> <span class="n">newcases</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">uniquecounty</span>
<span class="c1"># I drop all the NAs because that means that on the first day, there were no differences to count</span>
<span class="n">newcases_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">newcases_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Visualization-Code">Visualization Code<a class="anchor-link" href="#Visualization-Code"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>First off, I created a few variables needed in order to render the visuals correctly:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># inspired by </span>
<span class="c1"># https://github.com/github/covid19-dashboard/blob/master/_notebooks/2020-03-15-us-growth-by-state-map.ipynb</span>
<span class="c1"># to fix the altair transformation</span>
<span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">data_transformers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">disable_max_rows</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="c1">#https://github.com/altair-viz/altair/issues/1005#issuecomment-403237407</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">to_altair_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DateTime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">month</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">month</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">date</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">day</span><span class="p">,</span>
                        <span class="n">hours</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">hour</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">minutes</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">minute</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">seconds</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">second</span><span class="p">,</span>
                        <span class="n">milliseconds</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.001</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">microsecond</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># getting the maximum and minimum date</span>
<span class="n">dmax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DateOffset</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">days</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">dmin</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">min</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="c1"># getting the current_date</span>
<span class="n">curr_date</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">countycase_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># getting the topographic data</span>
<span class="n">url_counties</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&quot;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/deldersveld/topojson/master/countries/us-states/MN-27-minnesota-counties.json&quot;</span>
<span class="n">counties</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">topo_feature</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">url</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">url_counties</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">feature</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;cb_2015_minnesota_county_20m&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>In order to connect the three graphs, I created a variable <code>selector</code>:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># use selector</span>
<span class="n">selector</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">selection_single</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">empty</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;none&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fields</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;county&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">init</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="s1">&#39;county&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s1">&#39;Hennepin&#39;</span><span class="p">})</span>
</pre></div>
<p>I chose the empty field to be equal to 'none', in order to clear up the binding when I do not select any county. I also picked Hennepin county as the initial choice due to it being the highest number of cases. <a href="https://altair-viz.github.io/user_guide/generated/api/altair.selection_single.html">Altair's documentation</a> provides a good read on all the different arguments.</p>
<p>Here I created a variable <code>background</code> for the topographic map of Minnesota:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="n">background</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Chart</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">counties</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mark_geoshape</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">stroke</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;black&#39;</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">transform_lookup</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">lookup</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;properties.GEOID&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">from_</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">LookupData</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">dfmnlatest</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">key</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;fips&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
                         <span class="n">fields</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;county&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;cases&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;deaths&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;date&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">encode</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Color</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;cases:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">scale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Scale</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">scheme</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;greenblue&#39;</span><span class="p">)),</span>
    <span class="n">tooltip</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;county:N&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;cases:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;deaths:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">properties</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">width</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">500</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">height</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">350</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Total Confirmed Cases by County as of </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">curr_date</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_selection</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">selector</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">project</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;albersUsa&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
<p>I combined the topojson data with the <code>dfmnlatest</code> DataFrame using <code>transform_lookup</code>. I added the <code>selector</code> in the <code>add_selection</code> statement to connect it with the other graph. <a href="https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/schemes/">Vega</a> provided a nice selection of color schemes that can be used in the graph.</p>
<p>Here I created a variable <code>newcases</code> to graph the new cases throughout the duration of the Covid-19 data:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="n">newcases</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Chart</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">newcases_df</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mark_bar</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">properties</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">width</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">500</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">height</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">350</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;New Confirmed Cases by County&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">transform_filter</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">selector</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_selection</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">selector</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">encode</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">x</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;date:T&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">timeUnit</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;yearmonthdate&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
            <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Axis</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;%y/%m/</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelAngle</span><span class="o">=-</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">titleColor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;black&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span> 
            <span class="n">scale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Scale</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">domain</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">to_altair_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dmin</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">to_altair_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dmax</span><span class="p">)])),</span>
    <span class="n">y</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;newcases&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
             <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Axis</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;# of New Confirmed Cases&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">titleColor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;black&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span>
           <span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Color</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;county&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">scale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Scale</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">scheme</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;viridis&#39;</span><span class="p">)),</span>
    <span class="n">tooltip</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;county:N&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;date:T&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
             <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Tooltip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;newcases:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;# of new cases&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span> 
             <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Tooltip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;newdeaths:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;# of new deaths&#39;</span><span class="p">)]</span>
<span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
<p>The <code>transform_filter</code> tranform the filter based on the selection of our click. I used <code>Tooltip</code> wrapper for renaming the title of the column being grabbed from the <code>newcases_df</code> DataFrame.</p>
<p>Here I created a <code>chart</code> variable to show the breakdown of total confirmed cases in Minnesota:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="n">chart</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Chart</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dfmn</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mark_bar</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">properties</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">width</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">500</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">height</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">350</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;Total Confirmed Cases by County&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_selection</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">selector</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">encode</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">x</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;date:T&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">timeUnit</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;yearmonthdate&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
            <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Axis</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;%y/%m/</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelAngle</span><span class="o">=-</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">titleColor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;black&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span> 
            <span class="n">scale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Scale</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">domain</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">to_altair_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dmin</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">to_altair_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dmax</span><span class="p">)])),</span>
    <span class="n">y</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;sum(cases)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
             <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Axis</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;# of Total Cases&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">titleColor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;black&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span>
           <span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Color</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;county&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">scale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Scale</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">scheme</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;viridis&#39;</span><span class="p">)),</span>
    <span class="n">order</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Order</span><span class="p">(</span>
        <span class="s1">&#39;cases&#39;</span>
    <span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="n">opacity</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">condition</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">selector</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">)),</span>
    <span class="n">tooltip</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;county:N&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;date:T&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;cases:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;deaths:Q&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
<p>Finally, I created <code>final_chart</code> to combine all the three graphs together:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="n">final_chart</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">alt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">vconcat</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">background</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="n">newcases</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">chart</span><span class="p">,</span> 
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">resolve_scale</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">shape</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;independent&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">configure</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">padding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="s1">&#39;left&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;bottom&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">configure_axis</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">labelFontSize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">labelPadding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">titleFontSize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">configure_view</span><span class="p">(</span>
     <span class="n">stroke</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">None</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">final_chart</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
